<component id="ID_title01">
<text><![CDATA[Version]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_pop01">
<text><![CDATA[The IP version number. <br><br>]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_title02">
<text><![CDATA[IHL (Header Length)]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_pop02">
<text><![CDATA[The size of the packet header. Necessary because the Options field means the header size can vary and the protocol needs to know where the header ends and the data starts when processing the packet. <br><br>]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_title03">
<text><![CDATA[Packet Length]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_pop03">
<text><![CDATA[Size of entire packet, including header and data, in bytes. The minimum-length packet is 20 bytes (20 bytes header + 0 bytes data) and the maximum is 65,535 â€” the maximum value that this 16-bit field can have. <br><br>]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_title04">
<text><![CDATA[Identification]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_pop04">
<text><![CDATA[Uniquely identifies fragments of an original IP packet. <br><br>]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_title05">
<text><![CDATA[Header Checksum]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_pop05">
<text><![CDATA[Used for error checking the packet header. At each hop, the checksum of the header must be compared to the value of this field. If header checksum value does not match the calculated checksum then the packet is discarded. At each hop the TTL field is decremented and fragmentation is also possible, so the checksum has to be recalculated at each hop. Note: this checksum only applies to the header not the encapsulated data. <br><br>]]></text>
</component>

